────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Third-party dependencies and their licenses
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This product depends on, but does not redistribute, the following third-party
software. Each is fetched at build time via CMake `FetchContent`.

1. GoogleTest (https://github.com/google/googletest)
   License: BSD-3-Clause
   Used for unit and integration testing.

2. Google Benchmark (https://github.com/google/benchmark)
   License: Apache-2.0
   Used for micro-benchmarking (gated by QFAULT_RUN_BENCHMARKS=ON).

3. Stim (https://github.com/quantumlib/Stim)
   License: Apache-2.0
   Used as a stabiliser-simulation oracle for validation (Stage 2.5+).

4. MQT QCEC (https://github.com/cda-tum/mqt-qcec)
   License: MIT
   Used for logical equivalence checking (Stage 2.5+).

5. pybind11 (https://github.com/pybind/pybind11)
   License: BSD-3-Clause
   Used for Python bindings (Stage 5; QFAULT_ENABLE_PYTHON=ON).

6. GridSynth / newsynth (https://github.com/kenmcken/newsynth)
   License: BSD-3-Clause
   Wrapped at runtime as an external binary for T-gate synthesis. Not
   redistributed; see ADR-0013 for the v0.1 caveat that this is a popen
   wrapper (not native C++) and Stage 6 for the native replacement plan.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Excluded by design
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The following projects were considered as dependencies and **explicitly not
adopted** for license-compatibility reasons (per ADR-0015):

- liblsqecc (https://github.com/latticesurgery-com/liblsqecc)
  License: GPL-3.0-or-later
  Reason for exclusion: GPL-3.0 is incompatible with our Apache 2.0 licence.
  We re-implement A* lattice surgery routing in Stage 3 instead of vendoring.

